    "Untargeted attackUnlike a targeted attack, the untargeted attack is intended to disrupt the victim model in any way without any predefined objectives [44][45][46].",
    "This type of attack is intended to identify the vulnerabilities of the victim machine learning model irrespective of achieving any significant goals.",
    "Generally, these attacks are black box in nature and do not explicitly define any particular data points to be used for attack, rather than the adversary intends to degrade the overall performance of the attacked ML model.",
    "Subpopulation data poisoning attack [47] is one of the case studies of untargeted adversarial attacks on machine learning.",
    "Existing surveysThe research study [48] has surveyed the applicability and implication of adversarial attacks on machine learning-based cybersecurity applications, highlighting their impact."
